Co?op bank fleet Africa leasing limited has got off to a roaring start by concluding its first leasing deal worth over sh890 million. The new leasing firm is known in short as 'co?op bank fleet' is a joint venture between the Co?operative Bank of Kenya and global leasing specialist supergroup based in South Africa which operates locally through a subsidiary known as fleet Africa limited. This is part of a larger sh2.2 billion deal, entails the financing and delivery of a fleet of 125 vehicles to the ministry of interior, the national police service and the prisons department. Other sectors that are expected to drive high uptake of the leasing product include oil and gas, co?operatives, manufacturing, construction, transport, mining, and ICT.